#### 2. Add disconnect/reconnect toast notifications

Import sonner's `toast` function:

```typescript
import { toast } from 'sonner';
```

Add a `useEffect` that watches for disconnect/reconnect transitions in the tunnel status (from the `useTunnelStatus` hook or from the SSE sync events). The simplest approach is to track the previous connected state:

```typescript
const prevConnectedRef = useRef<boolean | null>(null);

useEffect(() => {
  const isConnected = tunnel?.connected ?? false;
  const prev = prevConnectedRef.current;
  prevConnectedRef.current = isConnected;

  // Skip initial mount
  if (prev === null) return;

  if (prev && !isConnected) {
    // Disconnected
    toast.error('Remote access disconnected', {
      description: 'Attempting to reconnect...',
    });
  } else if (!prev && isConnected && tunnel?.url) {
    // Reconnected
    toast.success('Remote access reconnected', {
      description: tunnel.url,
    });
  }
}, [tunnel?.connected, tunnel?.url]);
```

This effect should live in a component that is always mounted (not just when the dialog is open). Consider extracting it into a hook that is mounted in the App layout, or adding it to the `useTunnelSync` hook in `entities/tunnel`.

Alternative placement: Add the toast logic directly inside `useTunnelSync` in `entities/tunnel/model/use-tunnel-sync.ts`, since that hook is already subscribed to status changes:

```typescript
// Inside useTunnelSync, within the SSE event listener:
eventSource.addEventListener('tunnel_status', (event) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
  // Fire toasts on transitions
  if (data.connected === false && prevConnected.current === true) {
    toast.error('Remote access disconnected', { description: 'Attempting to reconnect...' });
  } else if (data.connected === true && prevConnected.current === false) {
    toast.success('Remote access reconnected', { description: data.url });
  }
  prevConnected.current = data.connected;
  // Invalidate queries
  queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['tunnel-status'] });
  queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['config'] });
});
```

